cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV

This paper proposes a novel exploration strategy for deep reinforcement learning that explicitly accounts for both parametric uncertainty and heteroscedastic observation noise. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on Atari games, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
